    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "DTC Explanation: P2A00"
    },
    {
      "type": "dtc",
      "code": "",
      "text": "DTC P2A00: LAF sensor Abnormal lean range characteristics"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection principle explanation"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "110_3.0_jpn_11033629_4.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The LAF sensor detects the oxygen concentration in the exhaust gas and outputs a continuous signal; the PGM-FI ECU calculates the air-fuel ratio from the LAF sensor output signal value and performs fuel feedback control to further improve the exhaust gas condition. The LAF sensor output voltage is monitored during deceleration with the throttle valve fully closed, and if the output voltage deviates from the normal oxygen concentration, the PGM-FI ECU determines a failure and stores a DTC."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Detection frequency, detection sequence, detection time required, detection method type, OBD status"
